§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A function $f: 𝗥^n → 𝗥$ is called a ❬real affine
    transformation❭ (or ❬affine transformation❭) if it maps an
    affine combination of two vectors to the affine combination
    of their results (with the same coefficients). ⦉
